OL,6,FThe report said: "It is encouraging to
OL,7,Fsee increasing recognition that
OL,8,Fchildcare is essential for
OL,9,Ffacilitating parental workplace
OL,10,Fparticipation, with the continued
OL,11,Fexpansion of funded childcare in early
OL,12,Fyears, support to develop wraparound
OL,13,Fchildcare before and after school, and
OL,14,Fthe introduction of free breakfast
OL,15,Fclubs.
OL,17,F"There is no longer an assumption that
OL,18,Fparents and employers are able to fit
OL,19,Ftheir work around the school day, or
OL,20,Fan expectation that they will do so.
